  <prompt>
    Execute the final triple-run validation gate for r2 per FR-15. Both test projects (`Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests` + `Spe.Integration.Tests`), 3 consecutive runs each = 6 TRX artifacts. Acceptance: `Failed: 0` across all 6.

    This task mirrors r1 task 084 (the canonical triple-run pattern). The protocol is unchanged; the surface is expanded (r1 task 084 was unit-only; this is both projects).

    Per NFR-05, triple-run validation is MANDATORY before phase exit. Per FR-15, the project cannot close (task 083 PR + admin-merge) until all 6 runs are green.

    If ANY run produces `Failed: >0`: HALT the wrap-up; investigate; do NOT proceed to task 083. The failure is a regression of Phase 1-4 work that must be resolved before close.

    If ANY run produces transient/flaky failures (passes in 2 of 3 runs): document in `baseline/final-triple-run-2026-08-XX.md` + quarantine the test via `[Trait("status","flaky-quarantined")]` + ledger entry. This is the acceptable transient-flake path.
  </prompt>

  <role>Validation AI agent executing the final triple-run phase-exit gate; producing 6 TRX artifacts + summary doc.</role>

  <goal>
    Six TRX artifacts + one summary doc:
    - **6 TRX files** in `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/`:
      - `final-triple-run-unit-1-2026-08-XX.trx`
      - `final-triple-run-unit-2-2026-08-XX.trx`
      - `final-triple-run-unit-3-2026-08-XX.trx`
      - `final-triple-run-integration-1-2026-08-XX.trx`
      - `final-triple-run-integration-2-2026-08-XX.trx`
      - `final-triple-run-integration-3-2026-08-XX.trx`
    - **Summary doc** `baseline/final-triple-run-2026-08-XX.md` with per-run counts (Total / Passed / Failed / Skipped / Duration); flake detection (any test that passes ≥1 + fails ≥1 across 6 runs); cross-reference to TRX artifacts.

    Acceptance gate per FR-15: `Failed: 0` across all 6 runs. If any flake, quarantine + document; failure here HALTS task 083.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="unit-test-project">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/</file>
    <file purpose="integration-test-project">tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/</file>
    <file purpose="r1-task-084-reference">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/tasks/084-* (if findable; canonical triple-run pattern)</file>
    <file purpose="r1-task-084-baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/ (r1's TRX outputs as format reference)</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/design.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-05">Triple-run validation required at phase exit (mandatory for FR-15)</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-15">Both test projects, 3 consecutive runs each, all `Failed: 0`. 6 TRX artifacts; zero variance reported</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-11">No test may end in `Failed` state at phase exit (predecessor pattern continues)</constraint>
    <constraint source="r1 task 084 pattern">Same protocol as r1 task 084 (canonical triple-run); 3 consecutive runs per project; capture TRX per run</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No `src/` or test logic modifications — measurement only</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/lessons-learned.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The triple-run pattern was canonized in r1 task 084: 3 consecutive runs of the same test project, capturing TRX per run, comparing for flake detection. Any test that varies between Pass and Fail across the 3 runs is flaky-quarantined (Skip + Trait + ledger entry) — NOT left as a sporadic failure.

      r2 expands the scope from r1's unit-only to BOTH projects. The integration suite (`Spe.Integration.Tests`) was triple-run validated at Phase 3 exit (FR-10) but this final gate ensures cumulative Phase 1-5 work hasn't regressed integration stability.

      The 6-TRX artifact set lives in `baseline/` as a permanent record of project close state. This is referenced by task 090 (wrap-up) + the exit-ledger.

      Per NFR-05, failure here is NOT optional — task 083 (PR + admin-merge) cannot proceed until all 6 runs are green. The gate exists because past projects shipped with "almost stable" suites and downstream consumers paid the cost.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="080" status="not-started">Phase 5 procedure doc update — must complete before validation</dependency>
      <dependency task="081" status="not-started">Phase 5 constraint extension (conditional) — must complete before validation</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/final-triple-run-*.trx (6 files)</file>
    <file>projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/final-triple-run-2026-08-XX.md (summary)</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify tasks 080 + 081 (and any earlier Phase 5 dependencies) are complete. Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` to confirm.</step>
    <step order="2">Build verification — `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` and `dotnet build tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/`. Both MUST produce 0 errors. If either fails, HALT.</step>
    <step order="3">Execute `Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests` triple-run: 3 consecutive `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --logger "trx;LogFileName=final-triple-run-unit-N-2026-08-XX.trx" --results-directory projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/` where N = 1, 2, 3. Capture each run's total/passed/failed/skipped + duration.</step>
    <step order="4">Execute `Spe.Integration.Tests` triple-run: 3 consecutive `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/ --logger "trx;LogFileName=final-triple-run-integration-N-2026-08-XX.trx" --results-directory projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/` where N = 1, 2, 3. Capture each run's total/passed/failed/skipped + duration.</step>
    <step order="5">Parse all 6 TRX files. Verify: Failed = 0 across ALL 6 runs. Flake detection: any test that passes ≥1 run and fails ≥1 run.</step>
    <step order="6">If `Failed: 0` across all 6: proceed to summary doc. If any run has Failed > 0: HALT; investigate root cause; report failure mode; do NOT advance to task 083.</step>
    <step order="7">If flakes detected (Pass ≥1, Fail ≥1): document each flake; apply `[Trait("status","flaky-quarantined")]` + Skip; add entry to a flaky-ledger (new entry); document in summary doc. This is the only allowed exception path.</step>
    <step order="8">Author `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/final-triple-run-2026-08-XX.md` with: per-run counts (6 rows: unit 1/2/3, integration 1/2/3); cumulative pass rate; flake detection results; cross-reference to TRX artifacts; verdict (PASS / HALT).</step>
    <step order="9">Verify `git status` shows: 6 TRX files (likely gitignored per root `.gitignore:58 *.trx` — that's expected); summary doc; potential quarantine commits if flakes found. Commit summary: "test(validation): final triple-run FR-15 — Failed: 0 across 6 runs" (or "test(validation): final triple-run + flake quarantine" if quarantine path).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Bash">`dotnet build`, `dotnet test` (6 invocations); TRX parsing; `git status`; final commit</tool>
    <tool name="Read">TASK-INDEX.md; TRX summary parsing</tool>
    <tool name="Write">summary doc</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="trx">6 TRX files in `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/` (likely gitignored per `*.trx` rule)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/final-triple-run-2026-08-XX.md (summary)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">6 TRX files generated: unit 1/2/3 + integration 1/2/3 — all named `final-triple-run-*-2026-08-XX.trx`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 6 runs show `Failed: 0` (HARD requirement per FR-15)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Summary doc `baseline/final-triple-run-2026-08-XX.md` exists with per-run counts + flake detection + verdict</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Any flakes documented + quarantined + added to flaky-ledger (if applicable)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Build verification clean: 0 errors on both projects before runs</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No `src/` or test logic modifications (verified via `git status`; quarantine commits are acceptable test-only changes)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Verdict in summary doc is PASS (otherwise task 083 BLOCKED)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    Run via `task-execute` skill. STANDARD rigor (validation gate; mechanical execution; no Step 9.5 quality gates beyond standard task hygiene).
  </execution>
</task>
